How a Computer Understands Text in NLP.

Main Idea

Computers cannot understand text directly.

Humans understand:

"I love Data Science"

But computers understand only:

101010... (numbers)

So NLP converts Text → Numbers (Vectors).

Process Flow
------------

Text
  ↓
Vectorization
  ↓
Numbers (Vectors)
  ↓
Machine Learning Model
  ↓
Prediction

Example
Input Text

"I love Data Science"

Step 1: Split into Words

["I", "love", "Data", "Science"]

Step 2: Convert into Numbers



| Word    | Number |
| ------- | ------ |
| I       | 1      |
| love    | 2      |
| Data    | 3      |
| Science | 4      |


Vector:

[1, 2, 3, 4]

Now the computer can process it.

Methods Mentioned in Slide
1. Count Vectorizer

Counts how many times each word appears.

Example

Text 1:

I love AI

Text 2:

AI loves Python

Vocabulary:


I, love, AI, loves, Python

| Word   | Text1 | Text2 |
| ------ | ----- | ----- |
| I      | 1     | 0     |
| love   | 1     | 0     |
| AI     | 1     | 1     |
| loves  | 0     | 1     |
| Python | 0     | 1     |


This table is called a Count Vector.

Use

Spam Detection
Sentiment Analysis
==========

2. TF-IDF Vectorizer

TF-IDF = Term Frequency × Inverse Document Frequency

It gives importance score to words.

Example

Document:

AI is good. AI is powerful.

Word "AI" appears often.

TF-IDF calculates how important "AI" is compared to all documents.

Use
Search Engines
Document Ranking
Resume Matching

==========

3. Hash Vectorizer

Converts words directly into numbers using a hash function.

Example
AI      → 234
Python  → 876
NLP     → 456
Use
Large datasets
Faster processing
Memory efficient


Real-World Example
Gmail Spam Detection

Email:

"Congratulations! You won ₹50,000"

Step 1

Text converted into vectors

[0.82, 0.45, 0.91, 0.12]
Step 2

Machine Learning Model checks pattern

Step 3

Prediction

Spam
Why Convert Text to Numbers?

Machine Learning algorithms such as:

Logistic Regression
Naive Bayes
SVM
Random Forest
Neural Networks

work only with numerical data, not text.

So:

Text
 ↓
Vectorization
 ↓
Numbers
 ↓
Model Training
 ↓
Prediction

=============

"Computers cannot understand text directly. In NLP, text is converted into numerical vectors 
using techniques such as Count Vectorizer, TF-IDF, and Hash Vectorizer. 
These vectors are then used by Machine Learning models for analysis and prediction."
